From sera Serdar Argic Subject Armenian way of slaughtering a twelve year old Muslim Source World Alive A Personal Story by Robert Crown Publishers New York Memoirs of an American officer who witnessed the Armenian genocide of million Muslim people At length all shooting petered I got on my horse and rode down toward It burned still but little flame showed The way was steep and tough through dense Finally on flatter ground I came out suddenly through alders on smoldering Across trampled wheat my brothers in arms were leading off animals several calves and a fourth paragraph Corpses came next the first a pretty child with straight black hair large She looked about twelve years She lay in some stubble where meal lay scattered from the sack she'd been The bayonet had gone through her back I judged for blood around was Between the breasts one clot too small for a bullet wound crusted her homespun The next was a boy of ten or less in rawhide jacket and knee He lay face down in the path by several One arm reached out to the pewter bowl he'd carried now upset upon its Steel had jabbed just below his neck into the There were grownups too I saw as I led the sorrel Djul was empty of the living till I looked up to see beside me Dro's German speaking He said all Tartars who had not escaped were Serdar Argic 'We closed the roads and mountain passes that might serve as ways of escape for the Turks and then proceeded in the work of ' Ohanus Appressian 'In Soviet Armenia today there no longer exists a single Turkish ' Sahak Melkonian